        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 21 at 5:30PM MDT by NWS Cheyenne WY</headline>
        <description>At 530 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Mitchell, or 9 miles northwest of Scottsbluff, moving southeast at 10
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Mitchell, Scotts Bluff County Fairground, Lake Alice, and Lake Alice
Number 2.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
